      "text": "> However, as Sandoval (2020) points out, while the ideas of platform cooperativism aim to subvert digital capitalism from the inside, there is always the danger of co-option. Beyond this, calls for even more radical shifts to platform commoning are appearing (Papadimitropoulos, 2021), which argue for a broader model of open cooperativism, premised on the principles of commons-based peer production that aspire to more circular and sustainable models of production, consumption and disposal."
